OL,3,CConcerns over two doctors sees 20
OL,4,Cpatient deaths referred to Coroner
OL,6,FMr Armstrong confirmed to ITV News
OL,7,Fthat no one has been sacked.
OL,9,FHe explains: "I don't think sacking
OL,10,Fpeople creates real change, I think
OL,11,Fthat makes people fearful and we've
OL,12,Fdone an awful lot of work trying to
OL,13,Fcreate a culture where people feel
OL,14,Fempowered and safe to speak up so
OL,15,Fsacking people isn't always the answer.
OL,17,F"Clearly, if an individual has a
OL,18,Fresponsibility to face then they need
OL,19,Fto, those are individual processes
OL,20,Fwith employees that we won't talk
OL,21,Fabout in public."
