OL,4,Cpatient deaths referred to Coroner
OL,6,FA separate audit also highlighted
OL,7,F"significant concerns" over the
OL,8,Fmedication given by these doctors to
OL,9,Fpatients between January 2019 and
OL,10,FJanuary 2022.
OL,12,FIt found there was no appropriate
OL,13,Fevidence for 153 people to be given
OL,14,Fanti-rheumatic and anti-inflammation
OL,15,Fdrugs - more than half of all the
OL,16,Frecords reviewed.
OL,18,FIn 38% of cases, these prescriptions
OL,19,Fwere then stopped following face-to-
OL,20,Fface appointments.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G6/10
